00:40:26.549 --> 00:40:27.967
Right. Okay, sir.

00:40:29.760 --> 00:40:32.930
<i>Sorry, the person you're</i> <i>trying to reach is not available.</i>

00:40:33.013 --> 00:40:34.974
<i>Please leave a message at--</i>

00:40:35.057 --> 00:40:37.893
<i>I already took care of the girl's body.</i>

00:40:38.602 --> 00:40:40.479
UNABLE TO ACCESS CONVERSATION

00:40:42.273 --> 00:40:44.859
CLOSE

00:41:02.376 --> 00:41:03.544
Contact them now.

00:41:06.130 --> 00:41:09.300
You saw. They blew up the chat already.

00:41:10.259 --> 00:41:12.344
So it's impossible to contact them now.

00:41:13.512 --> 00:41:14.513
Call them.

00:41:15.139 --> 00:41:17.850
-Do it. -How do you think this works?

00:41:18.476 --> 00:41:22.438
I can't do that. All I know is that the server's overseas.

00:41:40.331 --> 00:41:41.332
Come on.

00:41:45.961 --> 00:41:48.714
Please! Please don't kill me! I don't wanna die!

00:42:26.210 --> 00:42:28.754
HIGH SCHOOL GIRL'S BODY DISCOVERED

00:42:28.837 --> 00:42:31.090
MISSING HIGH SCHOOL GIRL FOUND DEAD IN THE WOODS

00:42:31.173 --> 00:42:34.718
HIGH SCHOOL GIRL'S BODY DISCOVERED UNDER A BRIDGE

00:42:37.012 --> 00:42:38.013
Damn it.

00:42:39.765 --> 00:42:42.768
This is your hair tie, right? It was on the ground.

00:42:44.478 --> 00:42:45.980
This belongs to you, right?

00:43:08.210 --> 00:43:09.378
Is Hye-ri asleep?

00:43:11.005 --> 00:43:12.214
I'm not sure.

00:43:12.298 --> 00:43:14.341
She's been in her room all day.

00:43:26.770 --> 00:43:28.606
Why didn't you come out if you're awake?

00:43:29.273 --> 00:43:30.774
I thought you'd greet me.

00:43:30.858 --> 00:43:33.694
Uh, I was just feeling tired. I'm sorry.

00:43:36.572 --> 00:43:38.907
What's with your face? What happened?

00:43:38.991 --> 00:43:41.327
I just tripped earlier today.

00:43:43.746 --> 00:43:45.789
That Min-ji girl did that to you, right?

00:43:46.540 --> 00:43:50.127
Ah, well, don't worry. Seriously, Dad, I'm okay now.

00:43:51.420 --> 00:43:53.130
Forget about that girl, okay?

00:43:53.213 --> 00:43:55.466
If you think about it, it's a little sad.

00:43:56.342 --> 00:43:59.637
She's such a vile person 'cause she wasn't raised right like we were.

00:44:02.556 --> 00:44:03.766
Do you know

00:44:04.767 --> 00:44:06.852
What kind of work her dad does for a living?

00:44:06.935 --> 00:44:08.062
Why do you ask?

00:44:09.980 --> 00:44:11.857
Because

00:44:11.940 --> 00:44:13.692
I'm just curious, I guess.

00:44:20.032 --> 00:44:21.033
Hye-ri.

00:44:22.451 --> 00:44:23.452
Yeah?

00:44:24.036 --> 00:44:26.038
Never let anyone step all over you.

00:44:26.664 --> 00:44:28.082
Make sure to fight back.

00:44:28.666 --> 00:44:30.417
And don't let anyone look down on you.

00:44:30.501 --> 00:44:32.920
Make them so scared, they can't look you in the eye.

00:44:34.338 --> 00:44:37.675
Make it so that just hearing your name makes everyone tremble with fear.

00:44:39.218 --> 00:44:40.344
That's how you be strong.

00:44:45.891 --> 00:44:46.934
Don't worry.

00:44:47.893 --> 00:44:50.521
If there's ever something that you need help with,

00:44:51.146 --> 00:44:52.523
I'll take care of it, sweetheart.

00:44:56.276 --> 00:44:59.154
<i>I've been thinking, boss.</i> <i>There's something I just don't get.</i>

00:44:59.863 --> 00:45:00.864
Which is?

00:45:00.948 --> 00:45:04.034
Why'd we let the daughter of the Chairman go and not get anything out of it?

00:45:04.118 --> 00:45:07.204
Isn't the Juhak Construction guy, like, seriously loaded?

00:45:07.287 --> 00:45:08.414
We could've held her hostage

00:45:08.497 --> 00:45:10.582
And blackmailed them for everything they've got.

00:45:11.709 --> 00:45:13.502
Honestly, I feel the same way, boss.

00:45:13.585 --> 00:45:15.254
Why did you just let her go?

00:45:16.255 --> 00:45:18.257
If you try to catch a snake without gloves,

00:45:18.882 --> 00:45:21.260
-you'll get bit on the hand. -What?

00:45:21.343 --> 00:45:22.761
Ju Gang-chan

00:45:25.139 --> 00:45:27.057
He's a cobra who will swallow you whole.

00:45:34.148 --> 00:45:36.150
<i>Ju Gang-chan is no ordinary man.</i>

00:45:37.568 --> 00:45:39.611
<i>He started out as a common street thug,</i>

00:45:39.695 --> 00:45:42.489
<i>and ended up taking over</i> <i>a huge construction company.</i>

00:45:44.116 --> 00:45:45.117
I'm sorry, sir.

00:45:45.200 --> 00:45:47.161
If you could delay construction one more time,

00:45:47.244 --> 00:45:49.288
I'll get the demolition done by the end of the month.

00:45:49.371 --> 00:45:52.040
That's the same thing you said last time you were here.

00:45:53.167 --> 00:45:55.043
Well, it's just that the owners hired thugs to

00:45:55.627 --> 00:45:57.004
I'm sorry, sir.

00:45:59.965 --> 00:46:01.550
Are you actually sorry?

00:46:02.301 --> 00:46:05.763
-'Cause it doesn't feel sincere at all. -Uh I am sorry.

00:46:06.972 --> 00:46:09.308
I mean it, sir, that's why I'm kneeling.

00:46:11.226 --> 00:46:12.686
What are you thinking right now?

00:46:13.479 --> 00:46:14.480
Sir?

00:46:16.231 --> 00:46:19.401
"Since I got down on my knees, he'll probably let it slide."

00:46:19.485 --> 00:46:21.695
"This is just what you're supposed to do."

00:46:23.363 --> 00:46:25.824
"So can this guy hurry up and forgive me already?"

00:46:28.118 --> 00:46:29.661
Am I wrong or is that what you're thinking?

00:46:29.745 --> 00:46:30.996
No way, boss.

00:46:31.079 --> 00:46:33.248
I sincerely wanted to apologize to you, sir.

00:46:33.332 --> 00:46:34.500
Okay.

00:46:34.583 --> 00:46:37.211
Then show me how sincere your apology truly is.

00:46:38.378 --> 00:46:39.838
<i>He calls them bodyguards,</i>

00:46:39.922 --> 00:46:43.342
<i>but he has a whole army of mercenaries</i> <i>who were former special forces.</i>

00:46:44.301 --> 00:46:46.428
<i>If money doesn't work, he uses violence.</i>

00:46:46.929 --> 00:46:47.930
<i>If that doesn't work</i>

00:46:48.013 --> 00:46:49.014
Wait!

00:46:52.226 --> 00:46:53.352
I'm sorry, sir!

00:46:54.102 --> 00:46:56.063
-Please forgive me. -Get lower.

00:47:14.498 --> 00:47:15.499
That's crazy.

00:47:16.542 --> 00:47:18.252
He's a psychopath for real.

00:47:18.335 --> 00:47:19.545
Um, boss.

00:47:19.628 --> 00:47:22.214
Then why did you decide to help with that girl's body?

00:47:22.923 --> 00:47:25.759
I owe the Chairman a favor. I already told you, didn't I?

00:47:25.843 --> 00:47:27.094
What favor?

00:47:27.177 --> 00:47:29.096
You don't need to know, you idiot.

00:47:29.179 --> 00:47:32.182
You're like a bear, always so curious and hungry.

00:47:32.266 --> 00:47:35.477
He's hairy too.

00:47:38.772 --> 00:47:41.608
Don't worry, Mr. Ju. I'll come see you soon.

00:48:18.770 --> 00:48:20.731
This is as far as I can go.

00:49:12.866 --> 00:49:15.994
Your brother was the best agent this unit had ever seen.

00:49:16.078 --> 00:49:19.039
He was capable of things no one else could even dream of.

00:49:19.122 --> 00:49:20.916
That's why the number 66

00:49:20.999 --> 00:49:24.461
Still symbolizes the greatest legend of the Republic, even now.

00:49:25.212 --> 00:49:27.297
But during a high-stakes mission,

00:49:27.381 --> 00:49:30.300
A traitorous rat stabbed him right in the back,

00:49:30.384 --> 00:49:32.260
And 66 died in action.

00:49:32.344 --> 00:49:35.263
That rat really betrayed his closest comrade

00:49:35.347 --> 00:49:37.516
And he left him there to die alone.

00:49:37.599 --> 00:49:43.230
That cockroach became Number 66 only to turn into a traitorous mutt of the South.

00:49:50.779 --> 00:49:54.324
I now give you 66, your brother's number.

00:50:00.831 --> 00:50:04.584
Go and bring me the head of the fake Number 66

00:50:04.668 --> 00:50:06.169
And avenge your brother.

00:50:37.451 --> 00:50:40.704
We haven't located the target yet, but we'll find him.

00:50:42.122 --> 00:50:43.165
Hold on.

00:50:44.416 --> 00:50:47.044
Here you go. It's the address of the police station

00:50:47.127 --> 00:50:49.463
Where they're holding his friend from the video.

00:50:50.047 --> 00:50:52.758
Oh. Uh, also

00:50:53.300 --> 00:50:54.468
Sorry to bring this up,

00:50:54.551 --> 00:50:57.429
But we haven't received any funds for a while now.

00:50:58.597 --> 00:51:00.807
Our comrades are really struggling out here, sir.

00:51:00.891 --> 00:51:03.310
So maybe after your mission,

00:51:03.393 --> 00:51:06.271
Would you be able to ask them to help us out?

00:51:07.522 --> 00:51:09.649
Comrade.

00:51:10.942 --> 00:51:13.487
The comforts of the South are expensive, aren't they?

00:51:19.326 --> 00:51:21.953
I'll leave the car key right here.

00:51:31.463 --> 00:51:32.839
42 MYEONGUN-RO, DOWON-GU, SEOUL

00:51:38.887 --> 00:51:42.099
I don't understand how he can sleep in a situation like this.

00:51:43.350 --> 00:51:44.726
He's like a wild animal.

00:51:45.769 --> 00:51:48.605
Why should I have to suffer because of that wild boar?

00:51:49.940 --> 00:51:53.401
From now on, if he calls me, I'll just let it ring and go to

00:52:10.168 --> 00:52:12.045
I'm just seeing things.

00:52:12.921 --> 00:52:14.714
I'm on edge because of that jerk.

00:52:19.136 --> 00:52:20.554
When will I get out?

00:52:26.393 --> 00:52:27.394
I'm starving.

00:52:31.731 --> 00:52:32.732
You awake?

00:53:02.554 --> 00:53:03.805
Excuse me, sir?

00:53:04.723 --> 00:53:06.183
Can I please have some food?

00:53:06.808 --> 00:53:10.270
Don't you think you should feed me if you hold me for hours? Huh?

00:53:10.353 --> 00:53:12.856
Even if I'm here sitting in a holding cell,

00:53:12.939 --> 00:53:15.775
I'd expect our great police force to make sure to feed their

00:53:15.859 --> 00:53:18.111
Oh! Finally!

00:53:18.195 --> 00:53:19.446
What took so long?

00:53:19.529 --> 00:53:21.823
Okay. Sir, thanks for your service.

00:53:21.907 --> 00:53:23.491
All right, what's on the menu today?

00:53:23.575 --> 00:53:24.993
Are you Park Jin-cheol?

00:53:26.828 --> 00:53:28.038
Who the hell is asking?

00:53:32.792 --> 00:53:33.960
That looks a little big.

00:53:34.586 --> 00:53:36.421
You should've found a better uniform.

00:53:36.504 --> 00:53:38.590
Don't make this hard. Where is 66?

00:53:39.341 --> 00:53:40.383
66?

00:53:42.427 --> 00:53:43.970
What is that?

00:53:44.054 --> 00:53:46.556
The number of the greatest agent of the Southern dogs.

00:53:46.640 --> 00:53:47.641
Oh.

00:53:48.642 --> 00:53:50.060
So you're from the North then?

00:53:51.853 --> 00:53:54.773
Well, you've come to the right place. Because that's me.

00:53:54.856 --> 00:53:56.858
You can't be serious.

00:53:57.442 --> 00:53:59.527
-You are not 66. -Why, thanks.

00:53:59.611 --> 00:54:01.321
A lot of people say I don't look my age.

00:54:05.408 --> 00:54:07.577
I think I've seen you too.

00:54:08.828 --> 00:54:09.996
Oh.

00:54:12.332 --> 00:54:14.167
This is you, right? Hmm.

00:54:14.793 --> 00:54:16.628
You think you're funny, shithead?

00:54:18.213 --> 00:54:20.423
Now I'm only going to ask you one more time.

00:54:21.007 --> 00:54:23.260
66, where is he?

00:54:23.343 --> 00:54:26.179
Wait, time-out. Aren't you being unfair with these civilians here?

00:54:30.183 --> 00:54:31.393
Fine. Hold on.

00:54:32.018 --> 00:54:34.020
789-9, Mangyun-dong.

00:54:34.604 --> 00:54:36.022
Second floor of Dowon Laundry.

00:54:36.106 --> 00:54:37.649
That's where he lives, okay?

00:54:39.442 --> 00:54:41.319
I expected that to be harder to get out of you.

00:54:42.153 --> 00:54:44.698
And I expected to eat, so we're both disappointed.

00:54:44.781 --> 00:54:46.741
You better kill him fast when you get there.

00:54:48.243 --> 00:54:49.327
If that's what you want.

00:54:49.411 --> 00:54:51.579
I'll kill him quickly for your sake, okay?

00:54:51.663 --> 00:54:53.164
When I get out

00:54:55.041 --> 00:54:56.418
I'm going to find you.

00:54:56.501 --> 00:54:58.128
You crazy asshole.

00:54:58.795 --> 00:55:01.298
Is there a problem? What's taking so long?

00:55:03.133 --> 00:55:04.134
Stay put.

00:55:06.261 --> 00:55:07.679
Huh? Hey, wait.

00:55:08.930 --> 00:55:09.931
Hey.

00:55:10.640 --> 00:55:12.392
Hold on. Stop!

00:55:12.475 --> 00:55:13.601
Shit.

00:55:13.685 --> 00:55:14.686
Hey, you!

00:55:15.270 --> 00:55:18.690
Sorry about this. I am sorry, sorry. I'm sorry.

00:55:18.773 --> 00:55:20.567
Whoa. What the hell?

00:55:20.650 --> 00:55:21.943
What's wrong with you?

00:55:22.027 --> 00:55:25.572
Oh, no. Hey, excuse me. This guy is dying. He's dying in here.

00:55:25.655 --> 00:55:28.033
Oh, my God. Are you okay? What's wrong?

00:55:28.116 --> 00:55:30.327
Come on, say something. He's not breathing!

00:55:30.410 --> 00:55:32.996
Breathe! CPR!

00:55:33.079 --> 00:55:35.999
-Officer! -What's happening?

00:55:36.958 --> 00:55:40.920
Come on, hurry up. He can't breathe. Oh.

00:55:41.004 --> 00:55:42.422
My gosh, can you hear me, sir?

00:55:43.173 --> 00:55:44.632
What's wrong? Are you hurt?

00:55:45.675 --> 00:55:46.801
Huh? Wait! No!

00:55:47.761 --> 00:55:50.305
-Open this door now! -I'm sorry, sir. I'll be right back, okay?

00:55:52.390 --> 00:55:55.101
Hey, wait! Stop!

00:55:55.685 --> 00:55:58.313
Man, this is fucking exhausting, you know that?

00:55:58.396 --> 00:56:00.523
But we have to do this.

00:56:00.607 --> 00:56:02.817
Hey, hey. Okay, enough.

00:56:03.401 --> 00:56:04.944
He'll die at this rate.

00:56:05.028 --> 00:56:07.906
All right, do you get it now, huh?

00:56:07.989 --> 00:56:11.076
Because of you, our construction project is about to fall apart.

00:56:11.159 --> 00:56:13.536
We gave you plenty of chances to leave, didn't we?

00:56:13.620 --> 00:56:15.538
Okay, I'll move out.

00:56:15.622 --> 00:56:18.666
See, that wasn't so hard.

00:56:19.250 --> 00:56:22.337
<i>So you're saying</i> <i>that you killed this girl?</i>

00:56:22.962 --> 00:56:25.131
<i>Get rid of her. Can you handle that?</i>

00:56:25.215 --> 00:56:26.674
<i>Whoa.</i>

00:56:26.758 --> 00:56:29.969
<i>I was just asking a question.</i> <i>Why are you talking to me like that?</i>

00:56:30.053 --> 00:56:31.596
<i>Don't worry about the money.</i>

00:56:31.679 --> 00:56:33.181
<i>I'll give you whatever you want.</i>

00:56:33.264 --> 00:56:37.060
<i>No way! I'm gonna pretend like</i> <i>I never heard this, okay? Now leave!</i>

00:56:37.894 --> 00:56:42.565
Wow, the power of a little editing, huh? Hmm?

00:56:44.067 --> 00:56:45.944
My acting's not that bad either.

00:56:47.404 --> 00:56:49.864
Should I become an actor now? Huh?

00:56:50.907 --> 00:56:53.368
All right, we got it, boss.

00:56:54.577 --> 00:56:57.872
Think I'm getting too old for this.

00:56:58.915 --> 00:57:01.418
I should just call it and retire now.

00:57:02.335 --> 00:57:03.336
Don't you think?

00:57:11.719 --> 00:57:13.430
Where'd you get the gun, sir? Sir?

00:57:13.513 --> 00:57:16.516
EVIDENCE ITEM NO. 9 - EVIDENCE ITEM NO. 10: MOBILE PHONE

00:57:18.059 --> 00:57:20.228
-I'm off now. Thanks. -Okay. Good work today.

00:57:20.311 --> 00:57:22.564
INTERROGATION ROOM

00:57:27.235 --> 00:57:28.278
He still won't talk?

00:57:29.070 --> 00:57:31.781
Yeah. We've been sitting here in silence, sir.

00:57:34.284 --> 00:57:36.619
Hey, mister. You can hear me, right?

00:57:36.703 --> 00:57:39.122
Just because a cop's power comes from a pen now,

00:57:39.205 --> 00:57:40.582
You think we'll go easy on you?

00:57:41.124 --> 00:57:42.375
What's your name?

00:57:43.334 --> 00:57:45.170
-Tell me your name now. -Come on!

00:57:45.837 --> 00:57:47.464
Do you think we wanna be here all night?

00:57:47.547 --> 00:57:49.549
-Just hurry up and-- -That's fine. Forget it.

00:57:49.632 --> 00:57:52.051
Just get his fingerprints and run him through the system.

00:57:52.927 --> 00:57:53.928
Yes, sir.

00:57:56.848 --> 00:57:57.891
Your finger.

00:58:14.782 --> 00:58:16.576
-Hey. Open the trunk. -Yes, sir.

00:58:23.041 --> 00:58:24.542
Geez, it smells like blood.

00:58:25.335 --> 00:58:28.046
Should've at least covered the girl!

00:58:28.922 --> 00:58:31.841
Why put a dead body in there without any plastic, you idiot?

00:58:31.925 --> 00:58:33.134
-I'm sorry! -Hey, rookie.

00:58:33.218 --> 00:58:35.386
-Get a bag. -I swear to God

00:58:36.679 --> 00:58:38.306
-Did you move? -Sorry, it's just

00:58:40.850 --> 00:58:41.935
Looks good.

00:58:57.158 --> 00:59:02.372
REQUESTING FINGERPRINT CHECK

00:59:07.252 --> 00:59:10.672
Listen, he's not the first asshole to make our lives hard.

00:59:10.755 --> 00:59:13.883
When I first joined the force, if someone acted like this, we would

00:59:13.967 --> 00:59:15.677
Um, never mind.

00:59:16.386 --> 00:59:19.222
-What the Captain. -What is it?

00:59:19.305 --> 00:59:20.431
ACCESS APPROVAL CODE REQUIRED

00:59:20.515 --> 00:59:21.766
"Access denied"?

00:59:23.017 --> 00:59:24.602
I don't know. Maybe I didn't put it in right.

00:59:33.444 --> 00:59:36.447
-Wait, is that his phone? -Yes, sir. It's with the evidence.

00:59:46.124 --> 00:59:47.250
"My daughter"?

01:00:08.313 --> 01:00:10.815
What the heck?

01:00:23.202 --> 01:00:24.203
Who is this?

01:00:31.210 --> 01:00:32.211
Min-ji?

01:01:14.170 --> 01:01:17.799
AGENT KIM REACTIVATED

01:01:18.675 --> 01:01:19.676
<i>Min-ji</i>

01:01:20.593 --> 01:01:23.596
I'm sorry for dragging you into this.

01:01:25.807 --> 01:01:27.558
<i>They came down from the North to kill you.</i>

01:01:27.642 --> 01:01:29.018
Let's rock and roll!

01:01:30.228 --> 01:01:31.646
<i>Min-ji could be in danger.</i>

01:01:31.729 --> 01:01:33.773
<i>Let's go find Min-ji. Come on.</i>

01:01:34.691 --> 01:01:35.900
<i>Get rid of the evidence first.</i>

01:01:37.443 --> 01:01:40.196
<i>Agent Kim's going crazy,</i> <i>looking for his daughter.</i>

01:01:41.823 --> 01:01:44.367
<i>The phone in your pocket,</i> <i>where did you get it?</i>

01:01:44.450 --> 01:01:45.993
<i>The girl from last night.</i>

01:01:46.661 --> 01:01:48.746
<i>Locate Agent Kim's daughter immediately.</i>

01:01:48.830 --> 01:01:50.331
<i>We need to get to her first.</i>

